						               													<description>RELICS&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Relics are large, non-elemental, metalic six-sided items. These ancient items are created from Eldrymetallum, a metal not native to Esfah.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Relics adhere to the same rules as items, described above, with two exceptions: &amp;#10;- As Relics are non-elemental, any unit may carry and use a Relic.&amp;#10;- A Relic is considered to be two items for the purposes of how many items a unit can carry and use.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Elemental Relic&amp;#10;- When rolled with an army, the Elemental Relic icon indicates which element units must contain to be affected by the relic. The SFR Logo contains all elements and ivory. &amp;#10;- Multiple Elemental Relics in an army may cancel each other. Elemental Relics that roll the same element have no effect on that roll. Note that the SFR logo matches all elements.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Elemental Relic  &amp;#10;During any non-maneuver roll, X health-worth of matching units in the army carrying this relic may be re-rolled once, ignoring the previous result, OR, you may recruit or promote X health-worth of matching units from your DUA to the army carrying this relic. Results may be split between recruiting, promoting, and re-rolling in any way you choose. Any promotions happen all at once.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
